Target URL: https://gozayaan.com/?search=hotel

## Task
Start from the hotel search page at https://gozayaan.com/?search=hotel

Execute this script to fill the search form and search for hotels:

```javascript
// Find and fill the location input
const locationInputs = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('input')).filter(inp => 
  inp.placeholder && (inp.placeholder.includes('City') || inp.placeholder.includes('Hotel') || inp.placeholder.includes('Area'))
);

if (locationInputs.length > 0) {
  const locationInput = locationInputs[0];
  locationInput.focus();
  locationInput.value = 'Sylhet';
  locationInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
  locationInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
}

// Wait a moment for dropdown
await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));

// Click on Sylhet option if it appears
const sylhetOption = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div, li, span')).find(el => 
  el.textContent.trim() === 'Sylhet' && el.offsetParent !== null
);
if (sylhetOption) {
  sylhetOption.click();
}

// Find and update check-in date
const dateInputs = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('input')).filter(inp => 
  inp.placeholder && inp.placeholder.includes('Check')
);

// Set check-in to April 16, 2026
if (dateInputs.length > 0) {
  dateInputs[0].focus();
  dateInputs[0].value = '16-04-2026';
  dateInputs[0].dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
  dateInputs[0].dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
}

// Set check-out to April 17, 2026
if (dateInputs.length > 1) {
  dateInputs[1].focus();
  dateInputs[1].value = '17-04-2026';
  dateInputs[1].dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
  dateInputs[1].dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
}

// Find and click search button
const searchBtn = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).find(btn => 
  btn.textContent.includes('Search') || btn.textContent.includes('search')
);
if (searchBtn) {
  searchBtn.click();
}
```

After the script runs:
1. Wait 3 seconds for results to load
2. Look for a star rating filter (usually shows 1-5 stars)
3. Click on the 5-star filter to show only 5-star hotels
4. Wait 2 seconds for filtered results
5. Extract all visible hotel names and prices in format: Hotel Name | Price
6. Return the complete list

